00:19:02.319 --> 00:19:06.319
Can LLMs be hosted in PINs to provide responses

00:19:06.319 --> 00:19:09.319
to reactive user inputs?

00:19:09.319 --> 00:19:13.319
I would say yes, asterisk.

00:19:13.319 --> 00:19:16.319
So, you know, with PINs,

00:19:16.319 --> 00:19:19.319
if it's an R object, you can pin it.

00:19:19.319 --> 00:19:23.319
Now, I would probably argue that it might be better

